Metric: Customer Churn Rate
Description: Percentage of paying customers at the beginning of the period who canceled their subscription during that period. Excludes trial-only accounts, plan downgrades, and involuntary churn from payment failures that are later recovered.
Owner: customer-success
Tags: churn, retention, saas, health-metric

Source: subscriptions, subscription_events

Given the customer had an active paid subscription at the start of the period
  And the subscription is not a free trial
  And involuntary churn from recovered payment failures is excluded

When we calculate
  Then count customers whose subscriptions moved to "canceled" or "expired"
  And divide by the total paying customers at the start of the period
  And multiply by 100

The result is "Customer Churn Rate"

Trust:
  Freshness must be less than 12 hours
  Null rate on status must be less than 0%
  Null rate on canceled_at must be less than 5%
  Row count of subscriptions must not drop more than 10% day over day
  Value must be between 0 and 30
  Value must not change more than 50% month over month
